    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1607068588,
    "creation_date" : 1607068588,
    "answer_id" : 65139852,
    "question_id" : 8088179,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here is working example in BDD style which is pretty simple and clear</p>\n<pre><code>given(carRepository.findByName(any(String.class))).willReturn(Optional.empty()).willReturn(Optional.of(MockData.createCarEntity()));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1096470,
      "reputation" : 29415,
      "user_id" : 1089967,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 59,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1f256b904ff621d678598d8fa49f86c5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "lance-java",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1089967/lance-java"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1698314315,
    "last_edit_date" : 1698314315,
    "creation_date" : 1613148470,
    "answer_id" : 66175809,
    "question_id" : 8088179,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use a <code>LinkedList</code> and an <a href=\"https://javadoc.io/static/org.mockito/mockito-core/3.2.4/org/mockito/stubbing/Answer.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Answer</code></a>. Eg</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>MyService mock = mock(MyService.class);\nLinkedList&lt;String&gt; results = new LinkedList&lt;&gt;(List.of(&quot;A&quot;, &quot;B&quot;, &quot;C&quot;));\nwhen(mock.doSomething(any())).thenAnswer(invocation -&gt; results.removeFirst());\n</code></pre>\n<p>Or perhaps</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>LinkedList&lt;Answer&lt;String&gt;&gt; answers = new LinkedList&lt;&gt;();\nanswers.add(invocation -&gt; &quot;A&quot;);\nanswers.add(invocation -&gt; &quot;B&quot;);\nanswers.add(invocation -&gt; { throw new Exception(); });\nwhen(mock.doSomething(any())).thenAnswer(invocation -&gt; results.removeFirst().apply(invocation));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 16045223,
      "reputation" : 81,
      "user_id" : 11580530,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1b65c1832aa6a6c06db4ac1ac6bea7fa?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "M S Kulkarni",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11580530/m-s-kulkarni"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1632413423,
    "creation_date" : 1632413423,
    "answer_id" : 69303494,
    "question_id" : 8088179,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is not directly related to the question. But wanted to put this in the same chain.</p>\n<p>If trying to verify the same method call with multiple arguments, you can use the below times feature by Mockito. You don't need it if you are not verifying.</p>\n<p>Mockito.verify(method, times(n)).methoscall();</p>\n<p>Here is 'n' is the number of times the mock is invoked.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2616743,
      "reputation" : 141,
      "user_id" : 2265660,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ceedc0bd7fdcc1cbb641d97f547cbe57?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Florent M.",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2265660/florent-m"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1637756380,
    "creation_date" : 1637756380,
    "answer_id" : 70095971,
    "question_id" : 8088179,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you have a dynamic list of values you can use <a href=\"https://javadoc.io/doc/org.mockito/mockito-core/latest/org/mockito/AdditionalAnswers.html#returnsElementsOf-java.util.Collection-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>AdditionalAnswers.returnsElementsOf</code></a>:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>import org.mockito.AdditionalAnswers;\n\nwhen(mock.method()).thenAnswer(AdditionalAnswers.returnsElementsOf(myListOfValues));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8460659,
      "reputation" : 2599,
      "user_id" : 6346531,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/75aa9d2cb0f4e6bdf16e80bb06d5f8f1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "aksh1618",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6346531/aksh1618"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1638865460,
    "creation_date" : 1638865460,
    "answer_id" : 70256927,
    "question_id" : 8088179,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This might be basic/obvious, but if like me you are trying to mock multiple calls for a method that is called unknown number of times per call to method to be tested, for example:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>public String method(String testArg) {\n    //...\n    while(condition) {\n        someValue = someBean.nestedMethod(); // This is called unknown number of times\n        //...\n    }\n    //...\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>You can do something like:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>@Test\npublic void testMethod() {\n    mockNestedMethodForValue(&quot;value1&quot;);\n    assertEquals(method(&quot;arg&quot;), &quot;expected1&quot;);\n    mockNestedMethodForValue(&quot;value2&quot;);\n    assertEquals(method(&quot;arg&quot;), &quot;expected2&quot;);\n    mockNestedMethodForValue(&quot;value3&quot;);\n    assertEquals(method(&quot;arg&quot;), &quot;expected3&quot;);\n}\n\nprivate void mockNestedMethodForValue(String value) {\n    doReturn(value).when(someBeanMock).nestedMethod();\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
